place.name: SUTTON MALLET
place.gazetteerText: SUTTON-MALLETT, a chapelry in Moorlinch parish, Somerset; 3 miles WSW of Edington r. station, and 5 E of Bridgewater. Post town, Bridgewater. Acres, 878. Real property, £2,642. Pop., 139. Houses, 29. The property is divided among a few. The living is annexed to Moorlinch. The church is modern. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
